ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: How much sense does this type of treatment make to you?
Notes: 0= No sense at all; 5= Some sense; 10= Perfect Sence

ElementDescription: How well do you think this treatment will work to help reduce your symptoms
Notes: 0= Not well at all; 5= Could go either way; 10= Very well

ElementDescription: How likely would you be to tell a friend or family member with similar symptoms to get this kind of treatment?
Notes: 0= Not likely at all; 5= Somewhat likely; 10= Very Likely

ElementDescription: How much do you think your symptoms will be reduced by the end of treatment?
Notes: 0= Not at all reduced; 5= Somewhat reduced; 10= Very reduced

ElementDescription: How important is it to you that you learn to manage your symptoms better?
Notes: 0= Not important at all; 5= About as important as most of the things I would like to achieve now; 10= Most important thing in my life

ElementDescription: How satisfied were you with the light treatment?
Notes: 1= Not satisfied at all; 10= Extremely Satisfied

ElementDescription: What was the best thing about the light treatment
What was the worst thing about the light treatment
